# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# XPS Intelligence — Vercel Environment Variables
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# WHERE TO SET THESE:
#   Vercel Dashboard → Project "xps-intelligence-frontend"
#   → Settings → Environment Variables
#   → Add each variable below
#
# ACCOUNT NEEDED:
#   Sign up:  https://vercel.com/signup
#   Team:     jays-projects-5febe7fa
#   Project:  xps-intelligence-frontend
#   Plan:     Hobby (free) is enough; Pro recommended for production
#
# SOFTWARE NEEDED (local CLI):
#   npm install -g vercel
#   vercel login
#   vercel link  (inside repo root)
#
# IMPORTANT NOTES:
#   • Vercel is the SECRETS VAULT for this entire frontend stack.
#   • ALL secrets live here — never in vercel.json (committed to git) or .env files.
#   • The Supabase Vercel Integration sets NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_* automatically.
#   • Set each variable for: Production, Preview, and Development environments.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION A — Build-time Variables (injected into browser bundle)
#
# These are safe public URLs — not secrets. They are baked into the compiled
# React bundle by vite.config.ts at build time via the `define` option.
# Set as: Environment = Production + Preview + Development
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Railway backend API URL — must end in /api
# How to get: Railway Dashboard → Project → your service → Settings → Domains
# Vercel UI path: Settings → Environment Variables → Name: API_URL
API_URL=https://xpsintelligencesystem-production.up.railway.app/api

# Railway WebSocket URL for real-time agent + scraper events
# How to get: same Railway domain, change https → wss
# Vercel UI path: Settings → Environment Variables → Name: WS_URL
WS_URL=wss://xpsintelligencesystem-production.up.railway.app


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION B — Supabase (set by the Supabase Vercel Integration automatically)
#
# Install the Supabase Vercel Integration ONCE and these are set for you:
#   https://vercel.com/integrations/supabase
#   → Add Integration → Select project "xps-intelligence-frontend"
#   → Select Supabase project "nxfbfbipjsfzoefpgrof"
#   → The integration sets NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and
#     NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in all Vercel environments.
#
# If setting manually (local or staging only):
# How to get: Supabase Dashboard → Project → Settings → API
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Supabase project URL — public, safe in browser bundle
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://nxfbfbipjsfzoefpgrof.supabase.co

# Supabase anonymous/public key — public (Row Level Security enforces access)
# ⚠️  This is NOT a secret — Supabase RLS, not this key, protects your data.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# SECTION C — Server-side Secrets (NOT in browser bundle)
#
# These are available ONLY inside Vercel Serverless/Edge Functions (pages/api/).
# Set as: Environment = Production (+ Preview if needed)
# Set as: Type = Secret (encrypted, never visible after saving)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Railway backend proxy URL — used by pages/api/ to forward requests to Railway
# How to get: Railway → Project → your service → Settings → Domains
# ❌ NEVER expose this in browser code — server-side proxy only
BACKEND_URL=https://xpsintelligencesystem-production.up.railway.app

# Groq API key — Vercel-native primary LLM for pages/api/chat.js
# Sign up:  https://groq.com  (free tier available)
# API keys: https://console.groq.com/keys → Create API Key
# ❌ NEVER expose in browser code
AI_GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Vercel Deploy Hook — triggers autonomous redeploy when Railway reports failures
# How to get: Vercel → Project → Settings → Git → Deploy Hooks → Add Deploy Hook
#   Name: "Railway Failure Recovery"  Branch: "main"
#   Copy the hook URL here.
VERCEL_DEPLOY_HOOK=https://api.vercel.com/v1/integrations/deploy/prj_xxxx/xxxxxxxxxx

# OpenAI key (optional — backup/secondary LLM)
# Sign up:  https://platform.openai.com
# API keys: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys → Create new secret key
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-proj-xxxxxxxx...

# Anthropic key (optional)
# Sign up:  https://console.anthropic.com
# API keys: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys → Create Key
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-api03-xxxxxxxx...

# Google Gemini key (optional)
# Sign up:  https://ai.google.dev
# API keys: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey → Create API key
# GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSy...


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW TO APPLY IN VERCEL DASHBOARD
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. Go to: https://vercel.com/dashboard
# 2. Select team: jays-projects-5febe7fa
# 3. Select project: xps-intelligence-frontend
# 4. Click: Settings → Environment Variables
# 5. For each variable above:
#    a. Click "Add New"
#    b. Enter the Name (e.g. API_URL)
#    c. Enter the Value
#    d. Select environments: ✅ Production  ✅ Preview  ✅ Development
#    e. For secrets (AI_GROQ_API_KEY etc): check "Sensitive" to encrypt
#    f. Click "Save"
# 6. Redeploy for changes to take effect:
#    Deployments → your latest → ⋮ → Redeploy
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# HOW TO APPLY VIA VERCEL CLI
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# vercel env add API_URL production
# vercel env add WS_URL production
# vercel env add BACKEND_URL production
# vercel env add AI_GROQ_API_KEY production   # will prompt for value (hidden)
# vercel env add NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL production
# vercel env add NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY production
#
# Pull all current env vars to a local file:
# vercel env pull .env.local
